race.comment: HOT DIGITY BOOM (1) looks well placed third up. Both runs back have been good, finishing fourth in each, both in stronger races than this. He got home fairly behind Porter who pinched a big lead at Flemington last time, in the market there. Comes back a notch now and should go close. INSAIN HARRY (12) is flying this time in, winning 2/3 and placing in the other. This is tougher than last start at Yarra Valley but he can measure up. KING TUT (10) resumes for his second campaign. He did win his maiden well on debut and showed ability thereafter. Watch the betting. ASAKURA (11) is lightly raced and won his maiden well enough fresh at Terang. He could go on with it. ZORRO'S FLIGHT (9) has been let up since a solid run fresh at Caulfield Heath. More ground here suits and his best is absolutely good enough.
